ike it he can drink a glass of tea with honei cake i think all thi will be enough for him he will be satisfi and sometim he will have fruit and candi he will have enough monei for a bath and to go to the movi to pai the apart expens and sometim to bui a littl present for the grandchildren i think the pension will support us he will be at peac he will have a roof over hi head he will alwai have someth to eat someth to wear he should have a certain minimum and it mean that some of the popul mai even live well veri well becaus peopl will have the opportun to work honestli and after that a secur old ag becaus there will be no more revolut and perestroyka in our countri we must put an end to all that and in order to put an end to it and secur a decent life for ourselv for sever hundr year to come we must make the transit to a new geopolit formula for the develop of the russian state we must accomplish thi surg of our to the south thi last southern dash the russian last campaign in order onc and for all to put an end to the danger on the fatherland s southern border and to help the peopl who ar russia s neighbor to gain a peac life and elimin all hotb of war and tension which lead to clash and conflict the southern campaign onc the red cavalri wa march on warsaw and thi wa the slogan forward to the english channel on to warsaw berlin the channel then our cavalri move to the east reach the pacif ocean where their march end in 1979 1989 the red armi went down to afghanistan and at on time in 1919 the cavalri wa march from the west via bulgaria to constantinopl and there wa no on in the path of thi cavalri onli the entent stop it progress and the take of constantinopl and in 1916 the russian reach the iraqi border and thei were in northern iran for mani year until 1946 i think so the advanc to the south is noth new for russia thi is a normal direct of movement for russia it militari structur and it econom and cultur institut we should feel comfort here both persian and turkm